dcterms:creator: M. Lichman
dcterms:description: The Australian Sign Language dataset consists of multivariate time series data collected from participants wearing instrumented gloves while signing specific words in Australian sign language. It contains 22 continuous attributes and 95 words with 27 examples each, focusing on eight selected words.
dcterms:title: Australian Sign Language Dataset

dcterms:description: The NMAC dataset contains simulated two-aircraft mid-air encounters, including 10,000 encounters with 863 near mid-air collisions (NMACs) and 9,137 non-NMACs. Each encounter has 77 attributes collected at 1 Hz for 50 time steps, representing various states and commands of the aircraft.
dcterms:title: NMAC (Near Mid-Air Collision) Dataset
